librjss

  Robust, zero-framework client library for Juragan Subsystem (JSS)
  authentication and API access. Provides cookie-based session management
  with automatic CSRF token extraction, retry logic, and full diagnostic
  tracing.

  Version: 1.0.0   License: MIT   Status: Early development

----------------------------------------------------------------
Installation
----------------------------------------------------------------

  [dependencies]
  librjss = { git = "https://github.com/mroczect/librjss.git" }

----------------------------------------------------------------
Quick start – CLI binary
----------------------------------------------------------------

  export JSS_BASE_URL=https://app.juragansejati.biz.id
  export JSS_EMAIL=user@example.com
  export JSS_PASSWORD=password
  export JSS_INSECURE_SSL=false          # set true only for dev
  cargo run --bin cli_auth

  The CLI authenticates, prints session info, and performs a test
  request to /api/method/frappe.auth.get_logged_user.

----------------------------------------------------------------
Project layout
----------------------------------------------------------------

  src/
    api/auth/          AuthEndpoints trait (URL builders)
    bin/cli_auth.rs    CLI login tool
    client/
      auth/            login, logout, session, token, app parser,
                       http helpers
      methods/         authenticated_get, post, put, delete
    handler/
      config/          AuthMode, ClientConfig, validation
      error.rs         JuraganError enum
      types/           FrappeBoot, SessionInfo, login/user info

  examples/
    jss_mock_server.rs    Full offline mock of JSS server for dev

  tests/
    api_auth_tests.rs     URL builder tests
    client_tests.rs       Integration tests against mock server
    env_tests.rs          Config validation tests
    error_tests.rs        Error type tests
    types_tests.rs        Deserialisation tests

  .github/workflows/ci.yml   CI pipeline (fmt, clippy, test, release)

----------------------------------------------------------------
Core concepts
----------------------------------------------------------------

  RjssClient
    Central client holding configuration, HTTP client, session, and
    credentials. Public API:
      new(config) -> Result<Self, JuraganError>
      authenticate() -> Result<(), JuraganError>
      logout() -> Result<(), JuraganError>
      ensure_session() -> Result<(), JuraganError>
      session_info() -> Option<&SessionInfo>
      authenticated_get(path) -> Result<String, JuraganError>
      authenticated_post(path, json) -> Result<String, JuraganError>
      authenticated_put(path, json) -> Result<String, JuraganError>
      authenticated_delete(path) -> Result<String, JuraganError>

  AuthMode (enum)
    Session { email: SecretString, password: SecretString }
    Token   { api_key: String, api_secret: SecretString }

  ClientConfig
    base_url: Url
    auth_mode: AuthMode
    expected_sitename: Option<String>
    required_roles: Vec<String>
    timeout_secs: u64           (default 30)
    max_retries: u32            (default 3)
    user_agent: String
    insecure_ssl: bool          (default false)
    Method: validate() -> Result<(), JuraganError>

  JuraganError (enum)
    Config(String)
    Validation(String)
    Network(reqwest::Error)
    Http { status, body }
    Auth(String)
    Csrf(String)
    Permission(String)
    SitenameMismatch { expected, actual }
    NotAuthenticated
    RateLimited
    Parse(String)
    Expired
    Cancelled

  SessionInfo
    sid: SecretString
    csrf_token: SecretString
    full_name: Option<String>
    sitename: String
    roles: Vec<String>

  FrappeBoot
    Deserialised from the frappe.boot JavaScript object found in the
    /app dashboard page. Contains user, sitename, csrf_token, and
    sysdefaults.

----------------------------------------------------------------
Environment variables (CLI)
----------------------------------------------------------------

  JSS_BASE_URL            Required.  Base URL of the JSS instance.
  JSS_EMAIL               Required for session auth.
  JSS_PASSWORD            Required for session auth.
  JSS_TOKEN_API_KEY       Required for token auth (if not using session).
  JSS_TOKEN_API_SECRET    Required for token auth.
  JSS_EXPECTED_SITENAME   Optional.  If set, login verifies the sitename
                          in frappe.boot matches.
  JSS_REQUIRED_ROLES      Optional.  Comma-separated roles that the user
                          must possess.
  JSS_TIMEOUT_SECS        Optional.  Request timeout in seconds (default 30).
  JSS_MAX_RETRIES         Optional.  Maximum retry attempts (default 3).
  JSS_USER_AGENT          Optional.  Custom User-Agent header.
  JSS_INSECURE_SSL        Optional.  Accept invalid TLS certificates (true/false).

----------------------------------------------------------------
Mock server for development
----------------------------------------------------------------

  Start the server:
    cargo run --example jss_mock_server

  It listens on http://127.0.0.1:8080 and replicates the exact behaviour
  of a JSS production instance: login response ("Logged In"), cookie
  setting, /app dashboard page with frappe.boot, get_logged_user,
  logout, and the missing CSRF endpoint (returns 417).

  Set env vars accordingly:
    export JSS_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080
    export JSS_EMAIL=dev@example.com
    export JSS_PASSWORD=password123
    export JSS_INSECURE_SSL=true

  Then run the CLI or integration tests. The library does not know
  the difference between mock and production.

----------------------------------------------------------------
Testing
----------------------------------------------------------------

  Unit tests (no server):
    cargo test --lib

  Integration tests (requires mock server running first):
    (terminal 1)  cargo run --example jss_mock_server
    (terminal 2)  JSS_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080 \
                  JSS_EMAIL=dev@example.com \
                  JSS_PASSWORD=password123 \
                  JSS_INSECURE_SSL=true \
                  cargo test --test client_tests

  All tests:
    Start mock server, then:
    cargo test --workspace

----------------------------------------------------------------
CI pipeline
----------------------------------------------------------------

  Located at .github/workflows/ci.yml. On every push or pull request to
  master:
    - Check formatting (rustfmt)
    - Lint (clippy -D warnings)
    - Compile check (cargo check --workspace)
    - Run unit tests (cargo test --lib)
    - Start mock server, run integration tests
    - Build release binary (cargo build --release)
    - Upload release artifact (cli_auth)

